a life in film helen whitney in conversation with marilyn yalom events at stanford a life in film helen whitney in conversation with marilyn yalom facebook twitter email print add to calendar helen whitney is an award winning filmmaker with over thirty years of experience producing dramatic features and documentary films her subjects have stretched across a broad spectrum of topics including youth gangs a portrait of the 1996 presidential candidates a trappist monastery in massachusetts the mccarthy era pope john paul ii and photographer richard avedon marilyn yalom is a senior scholar at the michelle r clayman institute for gender research a former professor and author of a history of the wife birth of the chess queen and the american resting place when wednesday november 9 2011 4 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where stanford humanities center board room map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading film humanities arts sponsor humanities center contact 650 724 8155 cbwillia stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 293 29339 more info last modified november 2 2011
